class Solution {
public:
    int bSearch(vector<int> arr, int target) {
        int l = 0, r = arr.size() - 1;

        while(l <= r) {
            int mid = l + (r-l)/2;

            if (arr[mid] == target) {
                return mid;
            }
            else if (arr[mid] < target) {
                l = mid + 1;
            }
            else {
                r = mid - 1;
            }
        }
        return -1;
    }

    bool checkIfExist(vector<int>& arr) {
        int n = arr.size();
        sort(begin(arr), end(arr));
        
        for (int i=0; i<n; i++) {
            int j = bSearch(arr, arr[i]*2);

            if (i != j && j != -1) {
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
        
    }
};



-----------------------------------
Algo:-
------------------

Algorithm:

Sort the array: Sort the given array in ascending order.
Iterate through the array:
  For each element arr[i]:
  Perform a binary search to find 2 * arr[i] in the sorted array.
  If 2 * arr[i] is found at an index j different from i, return true.
Return false: If no such pair is found after iterating through the entire array, return false.
Explanation:

The algorithm leverages the sorted property of the array to efficiently find pairs of elements where one is double the other.

Sorting: Sorting the array ensures that elements with the same value are adjacent, and it allows for efficient binary search.

Binary Search: For each element arr[i], a binary search is performed to find 2 * arr[i] in the sorted array. This is a more efficient approach than a linear search.

Checking for Duplicates: The condition i != j ensures that we don't consider the same element as both arr[i] and 2 * arr[i].
Time Complexity:

Sorting the array: O(n log n)
Iterating through the array and performing binary search for each element: O(n log n)
Overall Time Complexity: O(n log n)
Space Complexity:

O(1) extra space, as the sorting is done in-place.
This algorithm provides an efficient solution to the problem of finding a pair of elements where one is double the other in a given array.
